### [1 Kings (1 Samuel) Chapter 19](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#001.md)

[1 Kings (1 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa1 19:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa1 19:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#001.md), Jonathan discloses his
father's purpose to kill David; [Sa1
19:4](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#004.md), He persuades his father to
reconciliation; [Sa1 19:8](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#008.md), By reason
of David's good success in a new war, Saul's malicious rage breaks out
against him; [Sa1 19:12](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#012.md), Michal
deceives her father with an image in David's bed; [Sa1
19:18](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#018.md), David comes to Samuel in
Naioth; [Sa1 19:20](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#020.md), Saul's messengers
sent to take David, [Sa1 19:22](../../../bib/kjv/sa1019.htm#022.md), and
Saul himself, prophesy.

